  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to have better `swipe-to-delete` experience when interacting with chats on Home screen (same as I am used to when using other mobile messengers like Viber, Telegram, Whatsapp  or Skype)\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: currently `swipe-to-delete` gesture brings a bit poor experience to the user. Please check the following cases:\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n1. swiping is allowed only when user swipes in strictly horizontal manner but it is not always possible. I think we need to improve the swiping area and directions , so user wont be confused swiping again and again and thinking it is not working\r\n\r\n2. when swiping chat the screen is scrolled down very often (this is caused by point 1 i guess)\r\n\r\n3. disable `swipe-to-the-right` gesture as it does nothing (no use cases for this) and confuses user\r\n\r\n4. make the left `swipe-to-delete` gesture more smoothly (compare with Telegram or Viber). For now, it looks very amateurish \r\n\r\n5. Personally, I don't like the trash icon used - looks too old-fashioned, @denis-sharypin what do you think? Can we use the one Telegram uses? Or just a cross like Viber does?\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create any chat\r\n- Swipe-to-delete\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
